"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"## Thanks to the phenomenon of “multiples”\\n\\n[![Clive Thompson](https://miro.medium.com/fit/c/56/56/1\\\\*C6KlQUX7cSZiV7VlS12Vyw.jpeg)](https://clivethompson.medium.com/?source=post_page-----d64291cea550-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://clivethompson.medium.com/?source=post_page-----d64291cea550-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[Clive Thompson](https://clivethompson.medium.com/?source=post_page-----d64291cea550-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://marker.medium.com/who-was-first-with-a-big-idea-its-often-hard-to-know-d64291cea550?source=post_page-----d64291cea550-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[Dec 22, 2021·6 min read](https://marker.medium.com/who-was-first-with-a-big-idea-its-often-hard-to-know-d64291cea550?source=post_page-----d64291cea550-----------------------------------)\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/1\\\\*BFI8mAHuo8VKlsfJd1bduw.jpeg)\\n\\nGuglielmo Marconi invented radio in the 1890s — but so did Nikola Tesla and several others. (Photo by [Nicolas Buffler](https://www.flickr.com/photos/nicolasbuffler/16181342873/))\\n\\n[I recently wrote about the history of “pinch and zoom” ](https://onezero.medium.com/the-long-nose-theory-of-tech-innovation-de9227f98ddf)— and how Apple didn’t really invent it. Apple executives love to *claim* they did; Steve Jobs even [stood on stage and boasted “boy, have we patented it!”](https://www.theverge.com/2012/8/30/3279628/apple-pinch-to-zoom-patent-myth)\\n\",\"timestamp\":1641328375,\"title\":\"Who Was ‘First’ with a Big Idea? It’s Often Hard To Know\"},\"digest\":\"7lkGIxRdUF5DGskq49U41dYMciIhI8ylI4G-UAEg0bI\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x9308C52Cee23DF47566047FD5c8F1942577adD16\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"jdlfNPJc9-P7ahneteggtzEE_89riSloDh6TrzcaP1g\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"G8GKyDmBCgOZZibRhXVdGK4S3633wlofiS5RcKCiYhY\\\"}\",\"signat